record.text: From Molly Mielke’s newsletter… couldn’t agree more.. except that founders are taught to worship themselves and other founders who “did the impossible.” Those founders typically did not do it themselves and the narrative that they did is a signal of their god complex.

images.alt: Excerpt from Molly Mielke’s newsletter: the orientation of our belief seems to be the operative factor — where I work in a small subset of Silicon Valley, it’s common for belief to be turned inward. Founders are taught to possess enough faith to will whatever they’re working on into existence but they are rarely reminded to worship anything but themself. This creates a pressure cooker of responsibility that distorts reality to the point that they often find it hard not to confuse themselves for God — and we all know how that ends.
